public class SerializableHashSet<E extends Serializable>
extends HashSet<E>
implements SerializableSet<E>, Cloneable

Same as a HashSet, except that this class promises to be fully serializable.

Author:
Thomas Jensen

SerializableHashSet

public SerializableHashSet(@Nonnull
                           Collection<? extends E> pCollection)
Constructs a new set containing the elements in the specified collection. The backing HashMap is created with default load factor (0.75) and an initial capacity sufficient to contain the elements in the specified collection.

Parameters:
pCollection - the collection whose elements are to be placed into this set
Throws:
NullPointerException - if the specified collection is null

pLoadFactor - the load factor of the hash map
